column4:
“One of my all-time favorite hunting spots continues to be the Delta Marsh in southern Manitoba. These lesser scaup, or bluebills as they are commonly called, are coming in to feed on submerged vegetation just after a brisk late October squall.”

Limited edition of 750 signed and numbered art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 16-1/2" x 25". Framed size 29-1/4" x 37-1/2" with 3-3/8" espresso-finished moulding with gold edges. Double matting with harbor gray outer mat and brass nameplate. Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

In this classic painting the artist has stopped time for one crystal clear moment. The early morning air is crisp and clean. Hints of the coming winter have formed icy edges around the marsh. As the sun emerges from behind the barn a light in the window indicates that the farmer, as well as the mallards, are up and busy at the start of a new day.

Elite open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from 5 framing options.

Open edition of art prints featuring a yellow lab looking out over a lake during a sunset. Choose framed or unframed. Published exclusively by Wild Wings. Print size is 11"H x 14"W. Framed size is 13"H x 16"W.

column4: Open edition. Unique oval shape with soft, vignette edging for a dramatic viewing experience. Featuring fade resistant inks printed on durable, quality canvas framed in a light oak-stained wood moulding. Framed size 15" x 19". Published exclusively by Art Brand Studios.

column1: THE COLORS OF SPRING ART COLLECTION
column4:
“As the setting sun bursts through dense foliage, the colors of spring are beautifully illuminated. Above an altar of colorful flowers, songbirds rest and feed in this magical garden of plenty. Once again the season's annual rite of renewal is quietly celebrated.”

Limited edition of 9,500 signed and numbered art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 2 frame options. Also available; an artist proof edition of 950 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Encore open edition art print. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18". Choose from 4 frame options.

“The day is drawing to a close and the residents of this wilderness log cabin have moved inside for the evening. Two white-tailed deer, watching from the hill, see that all is clear and will soon venture down to feed in the open area.”

Pinnacle open edition art print excerpted from previous Redlin print editions. Image size, 20-1/4" x 11-1/2". Choose from 5 framing options.

Matey keeps a watchful eye on the horizon, waiting for the sun to rise and ready to retrieve whatever the tide brings in.

“Sportsmen and others who roam nature’s wild places will appreciate this scene. After hours of hunting, a father and son rest on the hillside as the retreating sun burnishes the landscape with its golden rays. The father and son silently share in one of nature’s memorable experiences. ‘It is one of those times I love best,’ the artist remembers, ‘a magical moment that has the power to create lifetime companions.’”

Limited edition of 29,500 signed and numbered art prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 2 framing options. (Artist proof available.)Open, unsigned edition from the Museum Canvas Collection. Image size, 23" x 39-1/2". Choose from 2 framing options. Elite open edition. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from 5 framing options. Open edition small framed linen print. Image size, 5-1/4" x 9-1/4".

The mood of the reef changes in an instant as a grey reef shark takes advantage of an unsuspecting reef fish. In a frenzied moment, other sharks in the vicinity quickly move in; but the now wary fish take cover. Frustrated, the sharks move out and the reef fish venture out again to feed on the drifting plankton; as their sheer numbers alone prelude to a sense of security.

Limited edition of 750 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 16-1/2" x 27". A Wild Wings exclusive.

column1: YOU SNOOZE YOU LOSE—GOOSE HUNTER ART COLLECTION
column4:
Any goose hunter who has laid behind a fence line waiting for geese to go out and feed can relate to this painting. One day they will fly at 7 a.m., and the next day it could be noon. After several hours of no action, it's easy to take a little nap and this is exactly when the geese decide to move!

Signature edition art print made from the original painting. Image size, 15" x 20". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

column1: LOCKED ON—NORTHERN PYGMY OWL ART COLLECTION
column4: Limited edition of 100 signed and numbered art prints and 100 signed and numbered canvas prints. Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

“All animals are curious. Deer are especially cautious, too. On this quiet summer day, Terry Redlin remembers the behavior of animals he watched in the fields as a kid. The rail fence serves as a protector for both the fawn and the colt, allowing them the safety in which to satisfy their curiosity. The doe, knowing all is well in front, turns her head to watch for predators. Note the small trio of wildflower blooms in the foreground. Nature has found the perfect protected spot for these wayward seeds to flourish.”

Limited edition of 9,500 signed and numbered art prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 2 framing options. (Artist proof available.) Elite open edition print. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from 5 framing options. Encore open edition canvas print. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from 2 framing options.

“The look and prowess of the tiger is compelling. I wanted to create an image that literally put the viewer nose-to-nose with this magnificent cat.”

Limited edition of 450 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 15" x 21". A Wild Wings exclusive.

“The look and prowess of the tiger is compelling. I wanted to create an image that literally put the viewer nose-to-nose with this magnificent cat.”

Limited edition of 450 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 15" x 21". A Wild Wings exclusive.

“The rural doctor did not work a nine-to-five job. Like the farmers he served, breakfast was before sunup and work already started as morning light broke over the horizon. But a country doctor’s demanding schedule offered clear advantages; the regenerative powers of solitude and nature, regular visits with old friends, and the satisfaction of knowing his efforts were appreciated.”

Pinnacle open edition excerpted from previous Redlin editions. Image size, 20-1/4" x 11-1/2". Choose from 5 framing options.

The ubiquitous sandbar shark patrols the wreckage of a sunken German aircraft on a shallow reef in the Mediterranean Sea.

Limited edition of 750 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 22" x 23-1/2". A Wild Wings exclusive.

For many, autumn is the most thoughtful season of the year. The trees and foliage have proudly displayed, and then quietly shed, their colorful apparel. The old wooden fishing boat has taken its last trip until spring. A great blue heron has made a final surprise visit. A pensive mood permeates the air. As nature slips into low gear, the more reflective among us are reminded of their own changing of the seasons.

Part of the Horizons Collection of horizontal, open edition prints, excerpted from previous Redlin releases. Image size, 8-1/2" x 27". Choose from 5 framing options. Also available; oval open edition print frome the Collage Collection. Framed size, 11" x 14".

“This painting captures the romance of a snowy winter night. Two deer have a clear view of the town below the hill. As the smoke from the surrounding chimneys wafts through the evening air, they slowly begin their nightly journey to the cornfield just beyond the bed and breakfast. We can see from the tracks in the snow, that this is their favorite route. The headlights encircling the skating rink tell us that the evening’s entertainment has begun. We can almost hear the muffled laughter and the scraping of skate blades on the ice. Although elements of this painting were inspired by the artist’s hometown, it is a familiar scene in hometowns across America.”

Limited edition of 3,500 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 2 framing options. Elite open edition. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from 4 framing options.

All work and no play make Lewie and Clark dull puppies! These two are so anxious to get to the park that they've fetched their own ride!

Open edition of 11" x 14" art prints are the perfect size to fill a smaller space in your home. Unframed. Published exclusively by Art Brand Studios. Made in USA.

“During high water years shoreline trees often succumb to the undercutting of waves. This blowdown position makes an interesting composition as the trees, like the geese, strain into the wind.”

Open edition art print made from the original oil painting. From the Encore Collection which features smaller image sizes than previous Redlin limited edition print releases. Image size, 8-3/4" x 14".

“While traveling through a rural area I became fascinated by the night combining. I stopped and wandered out into the fields and absorbed the flavor of its unique drama. While city dwellers sleep the farmer, when the crops are ready, responds to an age-old imperative.”

Horizon open edition art print exceprted from a previous Redlin limited edition print release. Image size, 8-1/2" x 27". Choose from 5 framing options.

“I have seen all the problems this old buck has lived through in either photos, mounted or live deer. The barbed wire in the rack, the broken tine, the bullet hole in a brow point, and all the rest are real injuries a wild buck could experience. For a single buck to have all of these battle scars, he would, no doubt, be an old warrior!”

Premier giclee canvas edition of 50 signed and numbered canvases. Image size, 26" x 42". A Wild Wings exclusive.

The spectacular waterways of the Pacific Northwest inspired me to paint this bald eagle. I wanted to instill in the viewer a sense of power both in the beat of the eagles wings and of the pounding waters of the falls beyond.

“This is one of those rare evenings when silence is truly golden. As the Canadian honkers swoop low over the farmstead, the only sound is the night air over their wings. Those who have experienced this magic moment count it among their most cherished memories.”

Open edition art print from the Encore II Collection which offers smaller versions of previous Redlin limited edition print releases. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18". Choose from 6 framing options. Fall woods setting with a quiet stream flowing through it needed only one additional element, wildlife. I chose Wild Turkeys. The three gobblers are harvesting acorns from oaks above.

Limited edition of 750 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 17" x 25". A Wild Wings exclusive.

"'School Daze' will undoubtly be my signature piece. These six sporting puppies have charmed many and their popularity continues to grow. It is very rewarding to watch the smiles appear when this print is shown."

Signature edition art print made from the original watercolor painting. Image size, 16" x 26".

“Now early autumn, the falling leaves carpet the ground with the colors of the season. The store owner is lowering the flag for the evening and the children are gone now-probably back to school. The dogs are still around, they have learned over the past few months that the store owner has table scraps from the restaurant in his bucket. The sounds of birds chirping and children laughing have been replaced with the quiet rustle of leaves and the gentle lapping of water on the shore. It is the end of a peaceful day and the beginning of a whole new season.”

Limited edition of 9,500 signed and numbered art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 3 framing options. Elite open edition art print. Image size, 14" x 24". Choose from 5 framing options. 00.

“In this nostalgic image Redlin revisits the sunny days of his youth. It was an innocent time when the most important thing in the world was to grab a pail and pole and hike out to the nearest fishing hole. The nearby bait shop offered ample refreshments for young appetites, including Langenfeld ice cream. The artist's wife was a member of the Langenfeld family, and the authentic sign is one of the personal touches we sometimes find in Redlin’s work.”

Artist proof edition of 2,490 signed and numbered prints. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Choose from 2 frame options. Also available; Encore II open edition (image size, 10-1/2" x 18"; choose from 4 frame options). Museum Canvas unsigned, open edition (image size, 23" x 39-1/2"; choose from 2 frame options). Open edition mini framed prints on linen. Choose from 2 frame options.

“In every outdoor person’s imagination is the ideal campsite, far from the tensions of modern civilization. In this quiet place the healing powers of nature slowly emerge and, for a few precious hours or days, all is right with the world. These campers have just arrived and rest in their tent. They are unaware of the Canada geese passing overhead on the way to their own resting place. Tomorrow our campers will, no doubt, be in touch with the magic of their surroundings.”

Encore II open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18".

“On this bright day the Canada geese are headed north, but have dipped low for a close inspection of a circa 1900 ‘sugar shack.’ The idea for this painting was inspired by mapler friends who, along with the artist, walked the shoveled paths and once again appreciated the rustic setting. Note the building’s functional design, suggesting an unknown architect’s anticipation of today’s solar homes.”

Part of the Horizon Collection of horizontal, open edition prints, excerpted from previous Redlin releases. Image size, 8-1/2" x 27". Choose from four framing options. Also available as an open edition miniature linen print. Image size, 5-1/4" x 9-1/4".

“In this idyllic scene, Terry Redlin paints the wonders of nature and the many caring people who work to maintain it. Here in a cathedral of over-arching trees, young students and their teachers consult the health of the river. The youngsters test the water’s purity and compare it with previous years. They collect samples of insect populations for signs of new arrivals. In this secluded setting, they learn how to preserve its pristine beauty. It is a tribute to conservationists, both old and those in training, who seek to preserve our environment for generations to come.”

Master Canvas edition of 960 signed and numbered canvas art prints made from the original oil painting. Image size, 18-1/2" x 32". Available framed. Elite open edition print. Image size, 16-1/2" x 28-5/8". Choose from 4 framing options.
A beautiful, nature inspired product that would be a great addition to any home!

“The peacefully feeding ring-necked pheasants have been caught off guard and break the still winter air with a flurry of sound and action. This corn patch was an actual field, hand planted and harvested with an old corn binder, then laboriously collected into large shocks. The artist found the setting a unique contrast to the straight rows and clean cuts made by modern farming equipment.”

Encore II open edition art print made from the original oil painting. Image size, 10-1/2" x 18". Choose from 5 framing options.

The old mill pond is an important symbol to many Americans. Its calm presence represents a less hurried time when life's ambitions were in proper perspective. Such a reordering of priorities is evident on this peaceful autumn afternoon. The mill owner has built a viewing platform overlooking the pond and, recognizing the moving water's healing power, often sits in the rocking chair listening to its soothing sounds.

" Horizon (horizontal) panoramic open edition art print. Image size, 8-1/2" x 27". Choose from 5 framing options.

column4: All is quiet as the peaks and valleys await the first touches of the sun. The glowing white orb barely shows itself, transforming the peaks and valley into a shimmering moment of sheer beauty. The mountain and valley all seem to come alive.

column1: CURIOUS COWS; END OF DAY ART COLLECTION
column4:
“There is a brief moment when I first come upon a group of farm animals when they are truly interested in me. But soon they realize I have no food and, having little interest in my artistic exploits, they walk away. The fleeting curiosity of these cows is matched by the fleeting last light of day, casting such wonderful shadows and creating the rich colors that give this small farm scene a natural glowing warmth.”

Limited edition of 750 signed and numbered art prints made from the original painting. Image size, 11" x 30-1/2". Published exclusively by Wild Wings.

column1: MASTER OF THE VALLEY ART COLLECTION
column4:
“Often only the imagination allows us to travel in search of needed respite. In this majestic landscape Terry Redlin’s art reaches one of these spiritual spaces, a pristine setting that relegates human strivings to their proper station. Here the grazing elk are prudent masters of their wilderness home, and also gentle reminders of the fragile nature of our environment.”

column4: As a gentle autumn fog lifts from the riverbank and in the valley, a whitetail buck and doe enjoy the tranquility of their surroundings. The only sounds to be heard are the gentle splashing of the river as the pair move upstream. It was my intent to have shades of foggy greens and grays create a tranquil mood.

“With the freshly cut Christmas tree aboard, the whole family is enjoying its ride on the big flat-bed sleigh. As they approach home, Grandpa has noticed two mallards nestled in by the river. The family dog trails along, part of the festive group but alert to his own agenda.”

The farmer means no harm, and on this fall evening wishes only to use the land on a temporary basis. He will soon willingly relinquish the territory to the wildlife and, as payment for the disturbance, offer the harvest leftovers.
